        <h1>LeetCode 1351: Count Negative Numbers in a Sorted Matrix (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                Given a m x n matrix grid which is sorted in non-increasing order both row-wise and column-wise, return
                the
                number of negative numbers in grid. The key insight is that the matrix is sorted both ways, so we can
                use a
                "staircase" approach starting from the bottom-left corner. When we encounter a negative number, all
                numbers
                to its right in that row are also negative. This allows us to count entire rows efficiently.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: grid = [[4,3,2,-1],[3,2,1,-1],[1,1,-1,-2],[-1,-1,-2,-3]] → Output: 8. There are 8 negative
                numbers
                in the matrix.
                Input: grid = [[3,2],[1,0]] → Output: 0. There are no negative numbers.
                Input: grid = [[1,-1],[-1,-1]] → Output: 3. Three cells contain negative numbers.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int countNegatives(vector&lt;vector&lt;int&gt;&gt;&amp; g) {
        int n = g.size(), m = g[0].size();
        int i = n - 1, j = 0, res = 0;
        // Move like stairs from bottom-left
        while(i &gt;= 0 &amp;&amp; j &lt; m){
            if(g[i][j] &lt; 0){
                res += (m - j); // rest of row is negative
                i--;
            } else {
                j++;
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
};</code></pre>
